Jeremy Clarkson has agreed to keep quiet about his sacking from the BBC so the Top Gear Live shows can go ahead 'in good spirit' The global tour of the motoring show looked like it may face the axe . 
  BBC decided not to renew his contract and cancelled what remained of the series . 
  But the corporation and presenter have reached an agreement over the remaining live shows . 
  BBC Worldwide feared Clarkson would vent his anger at sacking during the shows . 
  The shows have been rebranded to Clarkson and Hammond Live . 
 